Quote:  <i>Miner's cage, chair, or cradle. </i>Any of these uses may be applied to the box on an endless rope used for crossing rivers. Trampers on the whole seem to prefer<i> cage.</i> The Australians use <i>flying fox. </i>
Notes:  Ruth Mason `Track and Trail'
